7 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
8 SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 309, L.D. 692, “An Act to Increase Support
9 for Statewide Emergency Broadcast Messaging”
10 Amend the bill by striking out everything after the enacting clause and inserting the
11 following:
12 'Sec. 1. Transfer. Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, the State
13 Controller shall transfer to the unappropriated surplus of the General Fund $250,000 on or
14 before June 30, 2026 and $250,000 on or before June 30, 2027 of the funds received
15 pursuant to the Maine v. Google settlement and deposited to the account established
16 pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 203-A to be used solely for
17 activities identified in the court decree and approved by the Attorney General. Funds
18 transferred pursuant to this section must be provided to the Maine Public Broadcasting
19 Corporation to align state funding more closely with the statutory requirement to provide
20 emergency broadcast messaging for public safety.
21 Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
22 allocations are made.
23 PUBLIC BROADCASTING CORPORATION, MAINE
24 Maine Public Broadcasting Corporation 0033
25 Initiative: Provides additional one-time funds to align state funding more closely with the
26 statutory requirement to provide emergency broadcast messaging for public safety.
27 GENERAL FUND 2025-26 2026-27
28 All Other $250,000 $250,000
29 __________ __________
30 GENERAL FUND TOTAL $250,000 $250,000
3217 '
32 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
33 number to read consecutively.
