SENATE AMENDMENT “ ” to S.P. 309, L.D. 692
1 SUMMARY
22 This amendment directs the State Controller to transfer to the unappropriated surplus
33 of the General Fund $250,000 on or before June 30, 2026 and $250,000 on or before June
44 30, 2027 of the funds received pursuant to the Maine v. Google settlement and deposited
55 to the account established pursuant to the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 5, section 203-A
66 to be used solely for activities identified in the court decree and approved by the Attorney
77 General. Funds transferred must be provided to the Maine Public Broadcasting Corporation
88 to align state funding more closely with the statutory requirement to provide emergency
99 broadcast messaging for public safety. It also strikes and replaces the appropriations and
1100 allocations section.
